ent with recent analyses of the observed\nproperties of z>0.5 X-ray galaxy clusters. By fixing the slope to the values\npredicted by simple gravitational collapse, we measure at high redshift\nnormalizations lower by 10-40 per cent in the L-T, M_tot-T, M_gas-T, f_gas-T\nand L-M_tot relations than the observed estimates.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 1 Jul 2004 16:08:50 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-10"}
